$ Excel: Data -> Sort & Filter -> Filter

With the *Filter*, it is possible to filter rows in a → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Range that meet given criterias.

If such a filter is in place, the Filter symbol is displayed with a gray background (even if no rows are actually filtered), as shown below:
gh|about-Excel|/GUI/Ribbon/tabs/Data/Sort-and-Filter/Filter/enabled.png||


sa:
  The → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/AutoFilter[`autoFilter`] object.
